A man from Marakwet West on Tuesday was charged with killing to sheep by “raping” them.  He was charged at Iten magistrate court. Hosea Kyeng is accused of bestiality with the two sheep in Kabomo village on Sunday night. He denied the charges before Iten magistrate Nelly Adalo. The two sheep belonging to farmer John Korir are suspected to have died from the sexual act. Kyeng will remain in remand after he failed to raise a Sh200,000 bond. The case will be mentioned on April 11 and heard on June 6.